    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-07-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="508" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <head>No. 504.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Señor <persName type="to">de
                                    Zamacona</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 5,
                                1881</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 6th ultimo, relative to the complaint of the
                            Mexican Government regarding cattle-stealing from Mexico by bands of
                            thieves domiciled in Texas, and to inform you that this Department will
                            do all that lies within its power towards checking these thefts.</p>
                <p>To that end I have addressed both the Secretary of the Interior and the
                            governor of the State of Texas in the matter, furnishing them with
                            copies of your note, and requesting that such measures as may lie within
                            their respective jurisdictions may be promptly and energetically adopted
                            to correct and prevent any abuses which may be found to exist.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
